Here's the convention for naming OTel span attributes in this codebase:

## Attribute Naming Convention

### 1. **Use OTel Semantic Conventions (semconv) where they exist**
Canonical OTel GenAI semconv attributes are used verbatim — no prefix, no modification:

| Attribute | Example Value |
|---|---|
| `gen_ai.system` | `"vllm"` |
| `gen_ai.request.model` | model name |
| `gen_ai.usage.input_tokens` | number |
| `gen_ai.usage.output_tokens` | number |
| `gen_ai.response.finish_reasons` | string[] |
| `gen_ai.operation.name` | `"execute_tool"` |
| `gen_ai.tool.name` | tool name |

### 2. **Emmy-specific attributes use the `emmy.` prefix**
For attributes that have no OTel semconv coverage, the convention is `emmy.<domain>.<key>`:

| Attribute | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `emmy.prompt.sha256` | SHA-256 hash of the prompt |
| `emmy.tool.args_hash` | Hash of tool arguments |
| `emmy.profile.id` | Profile ID (auto-stamped on every span) |
| `emmy.profile.version` | Profile version (auto-stamped) |
| `emmy.profile.hash` | Profile hash (auto-stamped) |
| `emmy.profile.variant` | Variant name (when applicable) |
| `emmy.profile.variant_hash` | Variant hash (when applicable) |
| `emmy.role` | Turn role context |

### 3. **Span names use the `emmy.` prefix**
- `emmy.chat` — chat completion spans
- `emmy.tool.<toolName>` — tool execution spans
- `emmy.<event>` — event spans (mirrors JSONL event names)

### 4. **Key design principle (from `span-factory.ts`)**
> "Rather than stamp the attributes ad-hoc at every call site (D-10 anti-pattern — inventing emmy-specific names where OTel semconv already has canonical ones), we funnel span creation through helpers and only add emmy-specific attrs where semconv has no coverage."

The `EmmyProfileStampProcessor` (a `SpanProcessor`) auto-stamps `emmy.profile.*` on **every** span at `onStart`, avoiding the need to manually set these attributes at each call site.
